subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes. Head-body 48-56 cm, tail 65-84 cm; weight 6-7 kg (males) and 5.
5-6 kg (females). The Sabah Grizzled Languris gray above and below, except white belly and inner surfaces of limbs, contrasting with black on hands and feet. Crown is gray, with a tall black crest on back of head and two frontal whorls. Facial skin is reddish, with bluish lips and a pair of distinct black spots on each side of the face, between eyes and mouth—a pattern sometimes seen in more contrastingly colored individuals of Hose’s Langur ( Presbytis hoset
).
